- Updated SVG snapshots for SOT-89-3 and SOT-89-5 to reflect changes in dimensions and pad placements.

title: Fix SOT-363 parameters and add test snapshots for KiCad parity
description: Updates the SOT-363 footprint parameters and adds a test for visual parity with KiCads footprint using automated SVG comparisons.
body: This pull request updates the SOT-363 footprint parameters and adds a new test to check for parity with KiCad's footprint. The main focus is to improve the accuracy of the footprint and ensure visual consistency with KiCad using automated SVG comparisons. Footprint parameter updates: * Updated the `w` parameter from 1.94 to 2.56, `pw` from 0.3 to 0.4, and `pl` from 0.7 to 0.65 in the `sot363` footprint definition to better match the reference design. Testing and validation improvements: * Added a new test `sot363_kicad_parity.test.ts` that compares the generated SOT-363 footprint against KiCad's version using SVG snapshots and boolean difference analysis to ensure visual parity.

title: Add Orthogonal Camera, refactor to context useCameraController pattern
description: This pull request introduces an orthogonal camera option to the 3D viewer, allowing users to switch between perspective and orthographic views. It also refactors the camera control logic to use a context-based approach, improving the overall architecture and maintainability of the code. The changes include updates to various components to support the new camera type and ensure that camera settings are persisted in local storage.

Adds a new SPICE analysis test (ngspice-spice-analysis03-half-bridge-rectifier.test.tsx) for a half-bridge        
rectifier circuit.                                                                                                

  The test uses ngspice as the simulation engine.

title: feat: Add support for inflating traces from subcircuit circuitJson
description: Add support for inflating traces from subcircuit components defined in circuitJson, allowing internal connections to be respected upon instantiation.
body:
This change introduces the ability for <subcircuit> components to inflate source_trace elements from a circuitJson
prop. This allows for defining pre-wired subcircuits and having those internal connections be respected upon      
instantiation.                                                                                                    

A new inflator, inflateSourceTrace, has been added to handle the creation of <Trace> components from source_trace 
definitions. The logic correctly traverses the group hierarchy within the subcircuit's JSON to construct valid    
hierarchical selectors for trace paths.                                                                           

A new test case has been added to verify that a trace connecting two resistors within a subcircuit's circuitJson  
is correctly inflated and rendered.

title: Implement SOT23W with example and snapshot tests
description: Adds support for the SOT23W footprint, including 3D rendering and snapshot tests for the component.
body: This pull request adds support for the SOT23W footprint to the project, enabling both 3D rendering and testing for this component. The main changes include implementing the SOT23W model, integrating it into the footprint selection logic, updating exports, and adding a snapshot test. ### SOT23W Footprint Support * Added a new `SOT23W` component in `lib/SOT-23W.tsx` that defines the 3D model for the SOT23W footprint, including chip body and lead geometry. * Integrated `SOT23W` into the footprint selection logic in `Footprinter3d` so it can be rendered when the `"sot23w"` footprint is selected. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R201-R202) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R12) * Exported the new `SOT23W` component from `lib/index.ts` for use throughout the codebase. ### Example and Testing * Added an example usage of the SOT23W footprint in `examples/SOT-23W.example.tsx`, demonstrating rendering with `JsCadView` and `ExtrudedPads`. * Introduced a snapshot test in `tests/snapshots/sot23w.test.ts` to verify correct rendering of the SOT23W footprint. ## 3D Render ## Ref https://www.allegromicro.com/-/media/files/datasheets/a110x-datasheet.pdf

title: Implement  SOT457 with example and snapshot test
description: Adds support for the SOT-457 surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system, including a new component, integration into rendering logic, and corresponding tests and examples.
body: This pull request adds support for the SOT-457 surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system. The main changes include implementing the new `SOT457` component, integrating it into the main rendering logic, and adding a corresponding test and example. **SOT-457 package support:** * Added a new `SOT457` React component in `lib/SOT-457.tsx` that models the 3D geometry of the SOT-457 package, including leads and chip body. * Exported the `SOT457` component from `lib/index.ts` for easy import elsewhere. **Integration into rendering system:** * Registered the SOT-457 footprint in the main `Footprinter3d` rendering logic, allowing `"sot457"` to be rendered using the new component. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R43) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R194-R195) **Testing and examples:** * Added a new test case in `tests/snapshots/sot457.test.ts` to verify that the SOT-457 footprint renders correctly and matches the expected PNG snapshot. * Created an example usage in `examples/SOT-457.example.tsx` to demonstrate rendering the SOT-457 package with `JsCadView`. ## 3D Render ## Ref https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/package-information/SOT457.pdf /fix #216

title: Implemented TO92 and added example and snapshot test
description: Adds support for the TO92 package to the 3D footprint rendering library, including implementation of the TO92 component, integration into the footprint renderer, and addition of an example and snapshot test.
body: This pull request adds support for the TO92 package to the 3D footprint rendering library. The main changes include implementing the `TO92` component, integrating it into the footprint renderer, and adding a corresponding example and test. ### TO92 Package Support * Added a new `TO92` component in `lib/TO92.tsx` to render the TO92 package as a 3D model. * Integrated the `TO92` component into the main footprint renderer by updating imports and adding a case for "to92" in `lib/Footprinter3d.tsx`. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R43) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R255-R256) * Exported the `TO92` component from the library entry point (`lib/index.ts`). ### Documentation and Testing * Added an example usage of the TO92 footprint in `examples/to92.example.tsx`. * Added a snapshot test for the TO92 footprint in `tests/snapshots/to92.test.ts`. ## Image [Screencast_20251111_195146.webm](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/82e0e6fc-958d-459b-83e9-51074634e07d) ## Ref /fix #213

title: Implement SOT363 with test and snapshot test
description: Adds support for the SOT-363 surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system, including a new component, integration into rendering logic, and tests for visual regression.
body: This pull request adds support for the SOT-363 (also known as SOT457) surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system. It introduces a new `SOT363` component, integrates it into the main rendering logic, and provides an example and a snapshot test for visual regression. **SOT-363 package support:** * Added new `SOT363` component in `lib/SOT-363.tsx` that defines the 3D model for the SOT-363 package, including chip body and leads. * Exported `SOT363` from the package index in `lib/index.ts` for public usage. * Registered `SOT363` in the main rendering logic in `lib/Footprinter3d.tsx`, allowing it to be rendered based on the `footprint` string. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R43) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R198-R199) **Examples and testing:** * Added a usage example for SOT-363 in `examples/SOT-363.example.tsx`. * Added a snapshot test for the SOT-363 footprint in `tests/snapshots/sot363.test.ts` to ensure rendering correctness. ## 3D Render This render is correct the problem is in foorprinter, this pr fixes https://github.com/tscircuit/footprinter/pull/418 ## Ref https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/package-information/SOT363.pdf /fix #218

title: feat: Adjust schematic voltage probe label alignment and arrow position
description: Adjusts the alignment of schematic voltage probe labels to be left-aligned and modifies the arrow position to point to the name when both name and voltage are present.
body:
This change enhances the rendering of schematic_voltage_probe labels for better alignment and clarity.             

  Labels are now left-aligned for improved readability.                                                          
  When a probe has both a name and a voltage, the arrow now points to the name, with the voltage appearing on the
   line below it.

title: feat: Support name property on schematic voltage probes
description: Updates the schematic SVG rendering to support the name property on schematic voltage probes, displaying the name as the probes label and formatting it with voltage if present.
body:
This change updates the schematic SVG rendering to support the name property on schematic_voltage_probe.          

  If a name is present, it is displayed as the probe's label.                                                    
  If both name and voltage are present, the label is formatted as "name voltageV".                               
  Updated tests to include cases for probes with names, and names with voltages (including 0V).

title: feat: Add vertical stack option for CircuitPreview
description: Adds a verticalStack prop to the CircuitPreview component, allowing for a vertical layout with the image preview on top of the code editor, and updates SPICE simulation examples to utilize this layout while hiding PCB and 3D tabs.
body:
Adds a verticalStack prop to the CircuitPreview component, which allows for a vertical layout with the image   
   preview on top of the code editor.                                                                             
  Updates all SPICE simulation examples to use this new vertical layout.                                         
  Configures the SPICE simulation examples to hide the PCB and 3D tabs, focusing the view on the schematic and   
   simulation graph.

title: refactor: Reorganize SPICE simulation documentation
description: Refactors the SPICE simulation documentation by moving it from the Advanced section to a new, dedicated SPICE Simulation category within the Guides, splitting the content into separate files for better organization and direct linking to examples.
body: This pull request refactors the SPICE simulation documentation by moving it from the "Advanced" section to a new, dedicated "SPICE Simulation" category within the "Guides". The single page, which previously used a tabbed layout, has been split into separate files for the introduction and each example. This improves organization and allows for direct linking to specific examples.

body: This PR adds an RC charging circuit example to the SPICE simulation documentation. This new example uses the default spicey engine. The documentation for has also been updated to clarify that spicey is the default spiceEngine.

title: Align KiCad net mapping with connectivity keys
description: Builds the KiCad net list from source netstraces keyed by each subcircuit_connectivity_map_key, propagates connectivity-derived net metadata to traces, vias, and footprint pads so rats nests appear in KiCad, and adds a regression test that asserts nets are created from connectivity keys and referenced across pads, segments, and vias.
body:
## Summary
- build the KiCad net list from source nets/traces keyed by each subcircuit_connectivity_map_key
- propagate the connectivity-derived net metadata to traces, vias, and footprint pads so rats nests appear in KiCad
- add a regression test that asserts nets are created from connectivity keys and referenced across pads, segments, and vias

## Testing
- `bunx tsc --noEmit`
- `bun test tests/pcb/basics/basics07-connectivity-map.test.ts`
